      "id": "mat_1_1_4_1",
      "title": "Greetings: How to Say Hello",
      "content": "Greetings are the first words we say when we meet someone. Choosing the right one depends on the **time of day** and **how well you know the person**. \n\n### 1. General Greetings\nThese can be used almost anywhere:\n*   **Hello:** Neutral and polite. Use it with anyone!\n*   **Hi:** Informal and friendly. Great for friends and family.\n\n### 2. Time-Based Greetings\nThese change based on the clock. It is a sign of respect to use the correct one:\n*   **Good Morning:** Used from sunrise until noon (12:00 PM).\n*   **Good Afternoon:** Used from noon (12:00 PM) until around 6:00 PM.\n*   **Good Evening:** Used after 6:00 PM until the end of the day.\n\n*⚠️ Note: 'Good night' is only used to say goodbye when leaving or going to sleep, never as a greeting!* \n\n### 3. Practice Samples\n**Scenario A: Meeting a friend in the morning**\n> **Person 1:** Hi, Sarah! Good morning!\n> **Person 2:** Hello! How are you today?\n\n**Scenario B: At a store in the afternoon**\n> **Shopkeeper:** Good afternoon! How can I help you?\n> **Customer:** Hello! I am looking for a book.\n\n**Scenario C: Meeting a teacher in the evening**\n> **Student:** Good evening, Mr. Smith.\n> **Teacher:** Good evening, David. Are you ready for class?"
    }
